      "rationale": "Equivalency of input parameters between validation and COU is addressed qualitatively through the relevance assessment above. Formal equivalency scoring is not required at MRL 2."
    }
  ],
  "hasWeakener": [],
  "hasDecisionRecord": {
    "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/decision/morrison-cou1-decision-2026",
    "type": "DecisionRecord",
    "actor": "https://uofa.net/synth/actor/morrison-credibility-assessment-team",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "The credibility assessment team has reviewed all 13 ASME V&V 40 credibility factors for the Morrison COU1 CFD hemolysis prediction model. Seven factors were formally assessed; six were scoped out as not required at Model Risk Level 2. Of the seven assessed factors, six achieved their required credibility levels. The Test Conditions factor achieved Level 2 against a required Level 3; however, the team determined that the combination of the two formally characterized validation operating points, the published prior data covering an intermediate operating condition using an equivalent geometry, the demonstrated near-linear hemolysis sensitivity across the operating envelope, and the conservative nature of the worst-case operating point selection collectively provide sufficient confidence to support the regulatory decision. The model's prediction error at validated points is well within the ± 25% acceptance band, the RH < 1 criterion is satisfied, and the overall credibility evidence is judged adequate for a Class II device at MRL 2. The assessment team, including the lead validation engineer and the regulatory affairs representative, unanimously recommends acceptance of the simulation evidence package in support of the 510(k) submission.",
    "decidedAt": "2026-04-19T00:00:00Z"
  },
